RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 49. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONARCA DE ORO was quickest to the first turn, set the pace then turned back SHILSHOLE BAY into the stretch and drew away driving. SHILSHOLE BAY pressed the winner then moved up to challenge into the second turn but outkicked to mid stretch and was an easy second. SODA SPRINGS broke out about three paths, chased the winner to the backstretch then saved ground but weakened in the final furlong. MADAM PRESIDENT had no speed and was always outrun..

ENTRY.NAME: Shilshole Bay
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, asked, moved to challenge, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Monarca de Oro
ENTRY.COMMENT: best speed, set pace, met bid 2d turn, clear driving

ENTRY.NAME: Soda Springs
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, chased pace, saved ground, weakened

Final Purse $30,000 plus nomination fees (approx. $35,000; total purse est. $60,000). Final to be run on October 8, 2023. Weight, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOWHERE TOO RUN chasing, strong late run. DA BROS CARTEL quickest, clear, tagged. WINAGIN chased, mild late bid. LITTLEROCKINRUNAWAY no rally. EL COOKIE lugged in early. JR ducked inward start, missed rail. IMA KNIGHT lugged out early. PARVEYOR forced inward start. CASANOVA ADASHA dull effort.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Claiming Purse 6500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEAVENS TO BETSY stalked early then inherited the lead when YANKEE PANKEE bolted, saved ground to the stretch and held driving. ZEPHYR CAT had no speed, bid two wide to the second turn then loomed a threat but was outkicked in the drive. SAINT HELEN tracked the pace, tried to rally three wide but finished evenly in the lane. MANY MEMORIES had no speed, was two wide on the second turn and closed mildly. YANKEE PANKEE had the best speed but bolted into the backstretch and remained extremely wide thereafter. UNLIMITED GLORY stalked the pace early then took up between horses into the backstretch and did not recover. DIAMOND LUSTRE had brief speed then bled, was eased and walked off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: brief speed, bled, eased, walked off

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked early, took up into backstretch, outrun

ENTRY.COMMENT: best speed, bolted, extremely wide trip

ENTRY.NAME: Saint Helen
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, asked 3wide, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Heavens to Betsy
ENTRY.OWNER: Garcia Alexis S and Franson Darby

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 6500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAKUNUI prompted the pace to the backstretch, moved past MYSTIC WOOD FORCE leaving the three eighths but crowded that one sliighlty then responded steadily to prevail. MYSTIC WOOD FORCE set the pace to the backstretch then was passed by HAKUNUI but checked a bit when that one went by, chased to the stretch but could not catch up. HASHTAG BAE tracked the pace to the far turn, was two wide to the stretch but lacked the needed late response. FORT YORK trailed to the second turn while two wide then picked off rivals in the drive. BOY HOWDY was four wide early, tracked to the second turn while three wide but came up empty in the drive. STANLEY RYDER had no speed and was not a factor. CAPES HOT ROCKET tracked in the early stages then saved ground but gave way. Following a steward's inquiry into the action on the far turn, HAKUNUI was disqualified from first place and placed second for interference to MYSTIC WOOD FORCE.

ENTRY.NAME: Fort York
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, off rail, picked off rivals

ENTRY.NAME: Capes Hot Rocket
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked early, saved ground, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Hakunui
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, bid 2wide, crowded foe, took lead, held driving

ENTRY.NAME: Hashtag Bae
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, roused 2wide, lacked needed response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 7200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMILING SALSA hustled to the front, set all the pace, edged away to the stretch and held driving. SASSY EINSTEIN was outsprinted early, rallied inside on the second turn and was gaining slowly. LEAD ACTRESS broke a bit slow, raced four wide to the backstretch then eased in, saved ground to the stretch but could not threaten the top two. CARDS N COFFEE also was away a step slow, hustled up to stalked the pace but lugged out six wide on the first turn and was wide thereafter. MO SUGAFOOT pressed the winner early, got outkicked while three wide on the far turn and tired. ASTOUNDING ABBY was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: D K'S CROWN had no speed, settled to the three eighths then set out after the leaders, swung out three wide then closed with a stout run to be along in time. MASTER RECOVERY tracked the pace to the second turn, was two wide to the stretch, battled gamely, could not stall the winner but got the nod for second. DAD BOD set all the pace from the rail to the stretch then responded in the drive but was bested for the win and nailed on the line for second. BABY FRANKIE had no speed, saved ground to the stretch but came up empty in the drive. PERSEVERANCE had no speed and was not a threat. WHATWASITHINKING pressed the pace for three eighths while two wide then gave way. N. K. ROCKET MAN broke out, hustled up to track the pace but also gave way in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 6500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligiblity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANNY MICHAEL tracked the pace to the second turn, was three wide then angled in into the stretch and closed fast on the rail to be along in time. ANTICIPATED dueled early then pushed past LET GEORGE DO IT but bumped that one, forcing him to steady, set the pace from the rail to the stretch then dug in but was no match for the winner. LET GEORGE DO IT had good speed but was bumped by ANTICIPATED nearing the backstretch, steadied then stalked to the second turn but weakened in the final furlong. LONGFORD tracked the pace from the rail to the second turn then came up empty. SCRATCH ME stumbled badly to begin, had no speed and was outrun. SMOKIN KEN also had no speed and never was prominent. The stewards conducted an inquiry into the incident between ANTICIPATED and LET GEORGE DO IT into the first turn and disqualified ANTICIPATED from second to third for interference.

ENTRY.NAME: Let George Do It
ENTRY.COMMENT: good speed, bumped, took up, stalked pace, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Anticipated
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, crowded foe 1st turn, set pace, responded, caught late

ENTRY.NAME: Danny Michael
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, bid 3wide, rallied, angled in, closed fast rail
